<subSubSection id="845D49578A7CB86A4FD6392818A1DF57" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="39674C3BDCB3C75F6524F300CCDDBBFE" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName id="45CB38CE1A2E3573C95B84AD2C1D713C" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">NOTHRIDAE</taxonomicName>
Berlese, 1885
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E8E98852A0146ACE1CBDFD8507B4A9BA" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="FDBE733D6EE07477D8F437E4ABF6BE97" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Grandjean (1954) separated the genus 
<taxonomicName id="03914F3ABBD2F0BE581123AE4B024E48" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothrus</taxonomicName>
from the 
<taxonomicName id="36815845A460B0A4ABF45A5ABBEF770C" class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Camisiidae</taxonomicName>
, and consequently created a family 
<taxonomicName id="29E8FB393FD2A6C323AA2BD380809B2C" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nothridae</taxonomicName>
. This family is distinctly different from the 
<taxonomicName id="4A845A41D4FFD5823A2420EC93A3392B" class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Camisiidae</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: the notogastral hair f1 is present in all stages; there is neotrichy of the epimeres; there are only 2 pairs of adoral hairs; there is no genital neotrichy; the aggenital hairs appear to be absent. Sellnick and Forsslund (1955) still classified the genus 
<taxonomicName id="2591E8AD1BED2EBE921B3DCF6CB0A288" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothrus</taxonomicName>
with the 
<taxonomicName id="CD9DAC245840D241A8C1B061186679A1" class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Camisiidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A8C5FC5FDD21AF1B4774836C74D22A9E" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Some misunderstanding has arisen about the names of the two families. The name 
<taxonomicName id="BE392E36CE946F63A05ECF8E73A68BA2" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nothridae</taxonomicName>
was originally created by Berlese (1885c, p. 5; 1885a, p. 126); Oudemans (1900a) emended it into 
<taxonomicName id="23FC208223E3E252BC2F1F7478941C46" class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Camisiidae</taxonomicName>
. Berlese (1896b) enumerated the following heterogeneous collection of genera as representatives of the 
<taxonomicName id="67E34D455D889C97224C2152A669846A" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nothridae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="DF2D65701025C7606202F0577D26D2FF" class="Arachnida" family="Ameronothridae" genus="Ameronothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ameronothrus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="819E8496E5BF68EB42B534279A3651A5" class="Arachnida" family="Hermanniidae" genus="Hermannia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hermannia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="15F8A4E20711871414DBBDF11F5568B3" class="Arachnida" family="Neoliodidae" genus="Neoliodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Neoliodes</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="937453DB7FD92C78012CDDC3F5E048D6" authority="Berlese, 1885" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lohmanniidae" genus="Angelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Angelia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DD141BF1529A05717619DCC75C4AB959" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothrus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4A7BBAAC3D137EEE1D32C29C06CF4EC3" class="Arachnida" family="Hypochthoniidae" genus="Hypochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hypochthonius</taxonomicName>
. Although Berlese (1885a) used the name 
<taxonomicName id="432B7063C26184193D8652B30855C6CE" authority="Berlese, 1885" authorityName="Berlese" authorityYear="1885" class="Arachnida" family="Lohmanniidae" genus="Angelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oribatida" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Angelia</taxonomicName>
in the sense of the modern 
<taxonomicName id="713FF68F4FE137D8AFF26ECEF88086AB" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothrus</taxonomicName>
conception, and 
<taxonomicName id="5095E9AA91BF4719CA684B8E0BFF789B" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothrus</taxonomicName>
in the sense of 
<taxonomicName id="1F6EB3AE4C38B0FBE72924121409C5E2" class="Arachnida" family="Camisiidae" genus="Camisia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Camisia</taxonomicName>
, Berlese must be considered the author of the name 
<taxonomicName id="7580441A4E9521C26CF059AD9A0E2A09" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Nothridae</taxonomicName>
. Below, the nomenclatorial reasons for the present use of the name 
<taxonomicName id="0680229554D73DAB7D152CB58CA3DC70" class="Arachnida" family="Nothridae" genus="Nothrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Nothrus</taxonomicName>
are dealt with.
</paragraph>
